---
description: Next.js frontend rules for SalesIQ (Admin Portal + Agent Portal)
globs: frontend/**, src/**, app/**, components/**, hooks/**, lib/**, stores/**
---

Frontend stack:
- Next.js 14+ (App Router)
- TypeScript (strict mode — no `any` types)
- Tailwind CSS 3+ (utility-first; no custom CSS unless absolutely necessary)
- Zustand (global UI state: auth, call state, notifications)
- TanStack Query / React Query (server state, caching, data fetching)
- React Hook Form + Zod (forms and client-side validation)
- Socket.IO client (real-time transcript, AI guidance, notifications)
- Twilio Client JS SDK (WebRTC outbound/inbound calls)
- Recharts (analytics charts and sentiment timeline)
- React Flow (lead flow designer drag-and-drop canvas)
- Axios with interceptors (HTTP client with JWT refresh logic)

Two portals — one app:
- **Admin Portal** (`/admin/*`): Tenant admins manage agents, leads, campaigns, call flows, routing, analytics, settings, audit logs.
- **Agent Portal** (`/agent/*`): Sales reps see call queue, live call UI, AI guidance, deal predictions, coaching.
- Both portals share the same design system, component library, API client, and layout shell.
- Role-based routing and layout: middleware redirects based on JWT role claim.

Frontend rules:
- Use TypeScript strict mode for all frontend code.
- Keep components small, reusable, and focused on one responsibility.
- Keep presentation separate from data-fetching logic — use TanStack Query hooks in page-level components, not deep inside UI primitives.
- Use Server Components by default; Client Components only when interactivity or browser APIs are needed (mark with `"use client"`).
- Handle loading, error, and empty states explicitly in every page and data-consuming component.
- Preserve design consistency — extend the existing UI component library in `components/ui/` before creating new patterns.
- Support real-time updates via Socket.IO for live transcription, AI guidance, sentiment, red flag alerts, and notifications.
- Validate critical inputs on both client (Zod) and server (Pydantic).

Preferred frontend structure (established — extend, don't restructure):
- `src/app/(auth)/`          — Login, register, forgot-password pages
- `src/app/(dashboard)/admin/` — Admin portal pages
- `src/app/(dashboard)/agent/` — Agent portal pages
- `src/components/ui/`       — Reusable design system primitives (Button, Input, Modal, Table, Card, Badge, Toast)
- `src/components/layout/`   — Sidebar, Header, Breadcrumb, NotificationBell
- `src/components/calls/`    — Call-specific components (controls, transcript, guidance, scorecard)
- `src/components/leads/`    — Lead-specific components (table, card, import modal, flow canvas)
- `src/components/agents/`   — Agent-specific components (table, scorecard)
- `src/components/analytics/`— Chart components (kpi-card, conversion-funnel, leaderboard)
- `src/components/predictions/` — Deal pipeline, win-probability gauge, red-flag alert
- `src/hooks/`               — Custom hooks (use-auth, use-socket, use-call, use-live-transcript, use-notifications)
- `src/lib/`                 — API client (api.ts), Socket.IO setup (socket.ts), Twilio init (twilio.ts), utils, constants
- `src/stores/`              — Zustand stores (auth-store, call-store, notification-store)
- `src/types/`               — TypeScript domain types (models, call, lead, prediction, api)

State and data rules:
- Keep API client centralized in `lib/api.ts` — all Axios calls go through this instance.
- Normalize repeated API access patterns into TanStack Query hooks.
- Handle auth state carefully: JWT in memory, refresh token in httpOnly cookie.
- Never hardcode API base URLs in components — use `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` env variable.
- Zustand stores for global UI state only; server state belongs in TanStack Query.

Real-time rules:
- Socket.IO connection managed in `lib/socket.ts` and consumed via `hooks/use-socket.ts`.
- Join call rooms with `join_call_room` on call start; leave on end.
- Handle `transcript_chunk`, `ai_guidance`, `sentiment_update`, `red_flag_alert`, `call_status_changed`, `notification`, `deal_prediction_updated` events.
- Avoid re-renders on every transcript chunk — use refs or virtualized lists.

Do not:
- Mix many responsibilities into one component.
- Hardcode API URLs or Socket.IO URLs in components.
- Duplicate UI patterns that should be shared via `components/ui/`.
- Put admin-only flows in the agent portal routes.
- Use `any` TypeScript type anywhere.
- Use CSS modules or styled-components — Tailwind utility classes only.
